rdf:Description.lla:note: Apprenticeship expired on 1868-06-15 & taken in pay as [Ordy] on 1868-06-16.
Registry of Indenture on 1865-06-16 from Aberystwyth.
Wished to see the consul to be discharged, as the master refused to discharge him the consul denied him.
He came on board upon the ships landing in Leghorn and offered his services to the Master. He was engaged owing to the ship being short of hands following desertions.
Upon the ships landing in Leghorn, George came on board to offer his services and was engaged due to the ship being short of hands following desertions.
